To make the bruschetta, heat a griddle pan until hot. Drizzle the bread with the olive oil and griddle on both sides for 2 minutes.To make the saut√©ed mushrooms, melt the butter in a frying pan, then add the onion and garlic and cook until softened.Add the mushrooms, double cream, salt and freshly ground black pepper and cook for 5 minutes.To serve, place the slices of brie on the griddled bread and top with the mushroom sauce. Garnish with chopped parsley.